---

## Research Highlights

- Investigates the impact of packet loss on RTP audio streaming.
- Implements lightweight recovery mechanisms suitable for real-time applications.
- Compares the baseline RTP system with the enhanced system.
- Presents experimental results using approximately 11,437 RTP packets.

---

## Results

The proposed techniques significantly improve audio quality under low and moderate packet-loss conditions while maintaining real-time performance.

---

## Future Work

Potential future enhancements include:

- Reed-Solomon Forward Error Correction
- Adaptive bitrate streaming
- Opus codec integration
- AI-based Packet Loss Concealment
- Real-world WAN performance evaluation

